<p>Supposing i got a dataframe like this:</p>  <pre><code>dfA&lt;-data.frame(A=c(letters[1:3]),B=c(letters[4:6]),C=c(letters[7:9]))  &gt;dfA   A B C 1 a d g 2 b e h 3 c f i </code></pre>  <p>and another one like this:</p>  <pre><code>dfB&lt;-data.frame(replicate(12,sample(0:5,5,rep=T))) colnames(dfB)&lt;-sample(letters[1:9],12,rep=T)  &gt; dfB   a a d d g e i c i a g h 1 0 3 3 2 2 1 2 4 1 2 4 0 2 2 2 3 0 0 0 4 4 1 5 2 1 3 4 5 0 3 2 4 3 5 1 4 2 3 4 0 1 0 4 4 3 2 2 1 2 3 1 5 4 0 2 1 2 4 0 5 5 0 5 1 </code></pre>  <p><strong>How could I refer to all columns from dfB, which have names contained in column A of dfA?</strong></p>  <p>I am quite new to R and searched this forum a lot, but couldn't get the exact answer. I tried something like this: <code>sub&lt;-subset(dfB, !colnames(dfB) %in% dfA$A)</code> with unsatisfying results so far.</p>  <p>The output I'd wanna get would be:</p>  <pre><code>&gt; sub   a a c a 1 0 3 4 2 2 2 2 4 5 3 4 5 5 4 4 0 1 2 2 5 4 0 5 0 </code></pre>  <p>Can anyone help?</p>